**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Description:** The image shows a close-up view of the rear fender of a vehicle.

**Location of Damage:** The damage appears to be located on the lower portion of the rear fender, near the wheel well area. There is a noticeable dent and a small hole or puncture visible on the surface.

**Type of Damage:** The damage seems to be a combination of a dent and a puncture. The dent suggests that the metal has been deformed, possibly due to an impact or collision. The small hole indicates that there may have been a penetration from an object, such as a rock or debris, which has caused the paint to peel away and potentially penetrate the metal.

**Additional Notes:**
- The surrounding area of the dent and hole appears to have some chipped paint, indicating that the impact was not minor.
- The condition of the fender suggests that the vehicle may require repairs to restore its original shape and appearance.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained damage to the rear fender, specifically a dent and a puncture. The extent of the damage will need to be assessed further by inspecting the entire fender and possibly other areas of the vehicle to determine the full scope of the repair needed.
